SIMPLE: windy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Windy
<hw>Wind"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Windier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Windiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[AS. <ets>windig</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Consisting of wind; accompanied or characterized by
wind; exposed to wind.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>windy</xex> hill.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>M. Arnold.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Blown with the <qex>windy</qex> tempest of my heart.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Next the wind; windward.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It keeps on the <qex>windy</qex> side of care.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Tempestuous; boisterous; <as>as, <ex>windy</ex>
weather</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Serving to occasion wind or gas in the intestines;
flatulent; <as>as, <ex>windy</ex> food</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Attended or caused by wind, or gas, in the
intestines.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>windy</xex> colic.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Arbuthnot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>Fig.: Empty; airy.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Windy</xex>
joy.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Here's that <qex>windy</qex> applause, that poor, transitory
pleasure, for which I was dishonored.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wine</ent>⟦br⟧
